values:
SO for those of you who couldn't tell, I've mostly ditched eljay. That may or may not change, but the truth is that college is busy and I enjoy personal conversations with people vastly more, and if you would like to sustain that email me at laura.grabenstetter@gmail.com or IM me at jalopy05.

Otherwise, get off my back. It's rather rude to make assumptions about my personal decisions.

yargh. I just tried to make a friends group, and failed. Goddamn German formatting... But here's the deal: (I was mostly trying to filter out my out of state friends)

MY 18TH BIRTHDAY PARTY SATURDAY 1 O CLOCK STILL POND POOL ok? ok.

RSVP with a comment, plz. I'll be calling all of you whose numbers I actually know anyway.

Augh. No one comments on my entries. Depression.

EDIT: My friends are all CRAZ--I love them. Yay. ♥

I write too many poems about crappy relationships and sex with too little experience. Hm. Not that I'm complaining. Under the impression of stilted relations, love and denial and the wooden clap of a paint mixer sledging the color that burns on inside of your eyelids in that last moment of passion, wrecked with despair and screaming through your grocery list. Until, strewn in base listless lustlessness, veins pump sluggish ache on either end of damp sheets and blinking windows, and polluted prayers break through the sound barrier. Please, God, not again. Suggestions welcome. I orginally had a different idea for the last line involving domesticity, but it didn't pan out. I think as is it's a little anticlimatic, and I'm not sure if that's a good thing or not for this particular poem. *Note to self: email stories and poetry on old computer to self and save, transfer music too.

How You Life Your Life
You seem to be straight forward, but you keep a lot inside. You're laid back and chill, but sometimes you care too much about what others think. You're open to new people and friends, which makes you a pretty popular person. Some of your past dreams have disappointed you, but you don't let it get you down.
How Do You Live Your Life?
Your Love Number is
2

Of all the numbers, you are the most caring and empathetic lover. Unselfish and humble, you find it easy to forgive your sweetie's mistakes. At times, your need to please can be come a bit too needy. As long as you remain somewhat independent, your relationships are perfectly balanced.
What Is Your Love Number?
I got 120 on the IQ test, but I didn't even bother to paste it because I knew it was wrong.

I am so frustrated. Chester sent me an email saying he'd be home mid-day tomorrow, which means I've been waiting 2 days for him. I ditched helping tech for Country Club because I thought he'd come home today, and now I can't help them tech. I was a little reluctant anyway, and I was only asked yesterday, so I don't feel too horrible about it, but I really hope they find enough help and I feel bad for promising and ducking out on that. Oh well.

Deep breaths. I have 16 days before college, 16 days left with Chester, I am freaking out more than just a little. =[ I want reassurance that everything's gonna be alright, I want Chester with me. I don't want to have to start over. Yuck.

Good news is I got my first postcard from Chester today, it's gorgeous and half in German and I've already read it at least five times. A little sick of waiting though. It's not his fault entirely. I would have liked to have known so I didn't have to wait for him, but I wanted to be home when he came home, that's not obsessive, is it? 

Anyway, knowing a more exact when is a relief at least.

I am such a whiny bitch. But I miss Chester and he's supposed to be home today and I want him to call me and pick me up and kiss me and where IS he, it's so not fair. AUGH! 

The screen is really bright. *pout* And I haven't got anything to read. And damnit, where the hell is his phone call that goes "Laura, I love you, I'm back and I'm 5 minutes from your house!" And I talk too much about this, but I went all day without talking about it, instead I knit a whole scarf while waiting, partially because I was nervous but also because I had nothing else to do. It's kinda pretty. I'm giving it to Andrewm, because it doesn't match my coat and I made it all thick.

I watched Nurse Betty today, while knitting, funny, but SO BIZARRE. I love Morgan Freeman.

KAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHN!

The Rules 1. Leave me a comment saying, "Interview Me." 2. I will respond by asking you five questions. I get to pick the questions. 3. You will update your LJ with the answers to the questions. 4. You will include this explanation and an offer to interview someone else in the post. 5. When others asking to be interviewed comment, you will ask them 5 questions. 1. If you could have a pool full of jello and someone to swim in it with, what flavor would it be and who would be swimming with you? Well, jello doesn't really light my candle, so I'd say Chester just because it'd be fun and I've always been partial to raspberry. 2. Inspired by your icon: Which Disney princess was the luckiest in her fate? Little Mermaid, freedom from her family, her fabulous boy-toy and to eat her people and friends for the rest of her life. 3. You have 10 dollars worth of euro's, an ipod of your favorite music, the same magical water bottle Mika got, and a map. I drop you in Berlin. What's the first thing you do? Sell everything and bum around until I've gotten a job teaching in some provincial dorf and save up enough to send for Chester. That didn't make any sense, but it would still be killer fun. 4. Marry, fuck, or kill: Johnny Depp, Jude Law, Jake Gyllenhaal... I don't understand this exactly, but I'll say: Kill Jake Gyllenhaal (he reminds me of James Murray! GUH-ROOSS!), Fuck Johnny Depp and Marry Jude Law, because he could totally be a lifelong fuck. So hot. 5. You have to have a song stuck in your head for the rest of your life, what is it? Geez, I guess "Notorious" by Duran Duran because it's practically stuck in my head all the time anyway.

OMG SO EXCITED ABOUT CHESTER COMING HOME!

Went to Tina's this morning, watched Hide and Seek and The Hunchback of Notre Dame. It was fun. She's so bubbly. And we took a walk around her neighborhood tossing a tennis ball. It was really nice.

OMG her laptop is my laptop's twin! It's like so exciting! She named it Crowley, and I have to rename mine Aziraphale. Besides the problem of not being able to pronounce it.

I feel so scatterbrained right now. I need to finally plan my birthday party! Someone help me with that, k? k.

It is so suprising that I am going off to college so soon. 20 days. It's unbelievable. And only 18 more days with Chester before el great divide-o. Depressing. I don't have the energy to plan a birthday party! I don't particularily want to have one, either, don't like the idea of recieving presents or entertaining people for 3 hours or being dissappointed and anxious when no one actually comes. It would just require actually calling people, and I don't have any motivation. =/ But if Chester comes home before I've planned it, I won't. Time to get my ass in gear. I'm sure I'll enjoy it once it's here. Right? Right?

OhMyGee COLORS ARE SO BITCHIN'!

now for something icky. Don't read it if you're a boy or otherwise stupid.

Yeah, I really didn't have anything icky to say. Just wanted to see how many people who were boys or otherwise stupid clicked on it. You get rewarded with a picture! Of what, you ask...

Well you'll have to wait even longer for it, because my sister needs el interneto. DAAAAMN!

In conclusion, KAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHN!

I miss Chester. Unbelievably. There must be things that I don't like about him, that annoy me, that irritate me, but I cannot remember a single one right now, right now all that's blazoned in my memory are moments of quiet spent in his arms, swinging on the hammock or half-watching some muted telivision show in the backround, curled up on the couch.

And I want him right now. He's coming home in 3 days, and I'm sick of waiting, and at the same time I know that in college I'm going to have to go for a month or more without seeing him, (I mean, at least I'm going to be able to talk to him) but I don't want to even think about that.

Sorry, semi-incoherent rant, point being, I really miss him. =[ I feel like a baby for feeling this way though.

Whoever shot and did the musical scores for this movie is a genius. I lurve Jerry Mcguire! This movie alone makes me pant at the hottitude of Tom Cruise. And Renee Zellweger is so cute. I really want to knit Chester a scarf right now, I had started on one that was darkblue-grey, knit4 purl2 knit4, switch, knit2 purl3 knit2 until it became a legitimate force to be reckoned with. Anyway, hung out with Andrewm today. Rather pleasant. Later this week we're going to watch Schindler's list. AAAAUGH, WHY AM I WATCHING A MOVIE ABOUT RELATIONSHIPS WHEN I ALEADY MISS CHESTER SO MUCH? I am retarded. (Note to self; directions that I will never be able to access again if I don't save them here: Green Line Directions (More time on the Metro, less time walking) -Take the Orange Line to the Metro Center -Transfer to the Red Line -Take the Red Line to Gallery Place/Chinatown -Transfer to the Green Line -Get off at Mt. Vernon Square/7th Street -Walk south on 7th Street until you see the Warehouse Theater. ) Speaking of which, anyone want to come to The Country Club with me? I was thinking of going Friday night. Chester may or may not come, depending on whether or not he's doing something/has something he'd rather suffer through (no offense, he's just not what I'd call a theatre buff.) But it could be rather good. I expect no less from the actors, just the situation/s.

THIS is the first entry I am officially ever making with my NEW LAPTOP! How exciting is that!

It's an Inspiron 6000 Dell, whatever that means, and it is HUGE with a big ass screen and inset keys that are hard to type on and the  little scrolly mouse pad that no one likes, but I love it, and it's kinda ugly colored too. All of which is A.O.K., although it is kinda a bummer that it's both my graduation present and my only birthday present. I won't be greedy though, it's plenty enough just by itself. in any case, yay! Rejoice!

Also, I think that to transfer my music from my old computer to my new one, (since most of it is downloaded anyway) I shall just burn a whole bunch of themed CDs of the music that is WORTH saving and establish, through this transfer

1. a much less junked up computer/system
2. a way to transfer my music to Chester, who has the insane idea that he should just bring his weird transfer-y thing into my house and gather all my music that way. I don't understand computers well enough to consider it a real option, especially since when he first proposed it I thought he meant he was going to lug his whole computer over and set it up in order to get some music files and laughed my arse off at him.

I put German as one of the languages to install, and now I'm afraid all instructions ever are in German. eek! Well, that'll be one way to learn German REAL fast!

Good:
tina in her pajamas (sorry laura, she's the cutest asian ever. officially.)
loads of bubble tea and pork rice and crackers and wow. wow.
frisbee in the rain with lindsay =]
3 Disney movies with Tina

Bad:
Waking up at 6:00 am... aaaaugh...
The Infection... SUCH A SCARY MOVIE! Good, but too scary, with Jen
Not being hungry enough for a birthday dinner =/
Fighting with Jen while she drove me home about Gordon and Party and Crap.
Getting home and finding a package that made me cry...

Chester sent me a Pooh Bear doll with a big cupcake that sings Happy Birthday and wrote a sweet card to go along with it. I did not immediatley find the card, however, and tried to figure it out from the mailing instructions.

It said it was mailed from Ontario, CA, and it took me a few minutes to sort things out being as I, A. Don't know anyone who lives in California, and B. Thinking it kinda weird that there was an Ontario in California too.

and C., What the fuck is Chester doing mailing me something from Ontario? He's not in Canada!

Anway, the bear was a good but bad thing, something that made me happy enough that it made me sad, y'know? And now I'm still too frightened to go to sleep because of that damn movie and I really want to talk to somebody...

2. I'll tell you what song/movie reminds me of you.
3. I'll pick a flavor of jello to wrestle with you in.
4. I'll say something that only makes sense to you and me.
5. I'll tell you my first memory of you.
6. I'll tell you what animal you remind me of.
7. I'll ask you something that I've always wondered about you.
8. If I do this for you, you must post this on your journal. You MUST. It is written.
wish me a happy birthday! off to tina's, via lindsay, then off to dinner via jenny. and STILL afraid of ghosts thanks to andrewm. gr;ajkfdaksdf. o.O *twitch* TOTALLY couldn't sleep last night!

Your Rising Sign is Scorpio
You're so intense and passionate - you're on fire! You want to be an angel or a devil... you can't decide which. No wonder you seem moody and even a little dangerous. You've got some major mystery going on, so work it! Your personality is the strongest of all signs, making you hard to deal with. While you're ruthless to your enemies, you're loyal to your one true love.
What is Your Rising Sign?
Your Power Color Is Gold
At Your Highest: You are engrossed in passions that mentally stimulate you. At Your Lowest: You seek thrills and neglect what's important in your life. In Love: You see dating as adventure and approach it with an open attitude. How You're Attractive: You passion for life makes others passionate about you. Your Eternal Question: "Am I Having Fun?"
What's Your Power Color?
Your Kissing Purity Score: 34% Pure
You're not one to kiss and tell... But word is, you kiss pretty well.
Kissing Purity Test

1) Using your Current Initials, choose a different name for yourself: Lillith Esau Gottig (ok, fine, Esau is a guy's name, I just can't think of anything.) 2) If you were born outside of your era, when would you want to be born and why? The 20's, I'd make a wicked flapper or vamp. ;] 3) If you ran a store, what would you sell/have? I suppose books or corpses. It's toss up, really. 4) What part in a movie would you love to play? All and any, but if I had to choose one I'd love to play Tom Ripley in The Talented Mr. Ripley (another guy, I know, I know, but all these fantastic parts keep getting dished out to them!) 5) In your opinion, why do people suck? Eh. I'm on and off on this subject anyway. I'll go with the excuse that they're allowed to reproduce higgeldy-piggledy and that can't be too good for the human race when natural selection is taken out of the equation. 6) If you had your own state, what would you put on your new quarter? Hmmm... I think I'd be kicked out of the good'ole Union before they let me get to the whole quarter stage. 7) What's the oldest article of clothing you own? Oldest that I no longer wear is my green hospital gown with little clowns on it that I got when Warren was being born and threw a fit because I wanted to keep so much. Oldest that I do wear might be my red sports bra, I've had that since 5th grade and it was a hand-me-down from my cousin Melissa before that. 8) What piece of furniture have you replaced the most? Chairs? I really haven't. 9) What instrument do you wish you could be more than great at? PIANO!!! And singing. 10) Record, Tape or CD? CD 11) What do you think would be the best concert ever? Uh... I don't really go to concerts. No clue. 12) What is the best part of your favorite movie(s)? OOOHoohohho... The bit in The Talented Mr. Ripley where they're on the boat, and the bit at the end with Peter. OH YEAH, and Jude Law's ass. 13) What do you think is the most over-rated candy ever? Wonderballs, just because of how annoying that song is. Goddamnit, now it's stuck in my head... argh... 14) If you were writing out your will, who would you give your CD collection to? Probably Jen, she always gets a kick out of the stuff I burn her. But I'd give the musicals to Andrewm, first. 15) If you could only debate two topics the rest of your life, what would they be? Religon and Gay Marriage 16) Out of your friends, who would you say you are most jealous of, artistically? Tina. OOH and Emhen, for her guitar-singing-magic. 17) Most jealous of....intellectually? Hmm... Ben Leatherwood I guess. 18) What do you collect? Nothing fanatically, but I do keep all my old letters and postcards and love notes in a cigar box. 19) What is broken that you have, that you wish was fixed? My fish. 20) What do you do when you're home sick? I really don't, but I'll humor you: eat Cheerios and drink tea. 22) Story behind your username? Song by el Monkeys. 23) Current Favorite Article of Clothing? The pair of sweatpants I stole-borrowed from Amanda, Andrewm's sister. 24) Line from the last thing you wrote for someone? 'I miss you, you prick' to jen 25) A famous person you have met? Haven't. Cept Bill Nye once, that was kinda cool. 26) Favorite way to waste time? Chester. Tho I wouldn't call it wasting. 27) Last thing you bought yourself? postcards at the beach that I never sent... aaaaugh guilt guilt... made plans to help lindsay babysit for her little cousin-ish beings saturday night and possibly ramble about with tina saturday-day. was going to do something with jen sunday, not sure if that is off, yargh. going shopping for collegethings today with mother. wish me luck, the conversation went something like this: mom: I'm getting a new food proccessor today, you're coming with to get some college things. what do you need? me: ...? mom: like, clothes? anything you can think of that you need? me: socks. mom: yes, well. ok. I get the feeling that it will be a remarkably short trip. Still need to call back room/suitemates and find out who's bringing what, in the phone/microwave/fridge area. There are 7 of them. Fun.

suffocating. nothing works. miss chester... he's in eupope for 2 weeks whilst I mope in unbelievable suspense. It has turned me just a little crazy... Megan sent me a message in which every sentence ended with an exclamation point and I sent this back, perhaps a little over-the-top, I know, but honestly, it was a crime against humanity: that was an unbelievable amount of exclamation points congregrated in one place, megan. somewhere, a very emphatic fairy has curdled over it it's own fecal matter and surrendered it's life to that many exclamation marks. I do hope you're properly sorry. haven't sent, not to mention finished, most of the postcards I was too busy to finish at the beach, and they're boring a hole through my desk not to mention my conscience, but I really just don't to look at it. this birthday is going to suck butt if jen doesn't get her priorities straight, and it may suck in spite, no because of that if she's going to grumpy and inaccessible about everything. =[ I just don't want to accept anything's changed. finished the 6th arrpottah this morning. need to reread all of them, I spent the whole book wondering who tonks was and when ron had ever been a keeper before. ick. I want Chester. Goddamnit. birthday: 7.27.87. do something. (party after the 2nd, no way chester's missing that.)

Off to beach, ta!

muah muah!

In love with Se7en. Wow. Just, Wow. Offically haven't seen a movie that Brad Pitt ISN'T in in about 56 years. For instance, (not in order, because who can remember) Troy Mr. and Mrs. Smith Se7en Snatch and so much more that I can't remember. When did Brad Pitt start being in every movie ever? And, even worse, When did he start being a Not-So-Bad actor? Btw, Mr. + Mrs. Smith wasn't that bad of a movie, the best parts = Adam Brody sitting right across from Brad Pitt, being interrogated by him in fact, while wearing a Fight Club Tshirt. and Angelina Jolie: I'm Jewish. lol. right, like a baddass Jewish orphan is possible. The Typing Test type your name... with your nose-- laura grabenstetter big ole pointy jewish nose proves good for something with your chin-- laurza grab en st5e3t5terf not so much crappy non-existant chin with your tongue-- laura grabenstett with your eyes closed-- larua grabenstetter ew my keyboard is wet... with your lips puckered up in a kiss-- l0aura grabenstette with your toe-- lkauyera gfreabvebnsartertrtrewr wow my toes SUCK ASS now what I really should have done is learned how to use CTRl+C and CTRL+V. harumpfh. Tried to ask Parents about beach, and they twisted "andrew michel's family is going to the beach and have invited me and chester." to "laura's running off with her boyfriend" o.O =/ hrmpfh.

doctor: yeah, we can't give you half the shots you need, you're going to come back another time.
me: ... why?
doctor: because it's thursday.

Guess who's birthday is in 20 days? Super-swell legality. <strike>I haven't decided if posting a 'wish list' is too mercenary or flawed or presumptious yet, but if you ask I have plenty of ideas. ;]</strike> Party will probably be after my actual birthday, just because that bum Chester will still be in Austria then, but ideas for parties are welcome. I haven't had a real birthday party for years... Maybe provided I do all the work, someone would be willing to host a dozen rowdy guests in a party-like mass... eesh, not a tempting offer, but I can't have it here, so maybe a pool party or something. In any case, I'm looking forward to it.

Wishlist forthcoming, blame kgi.

PS, If you want me to send you a postcard from the beach, it's a relatively cheap and awesome to recieve shout-out, comment with your address, loves.

I ♥ Postcards.

Now the new problem is what to take in place of the 151 Math that I placed out of... Could go back to taking Chemistry with the lab that put me in the 19 classes bracket, all the seminars and cool classes are taken up, I don't want a higher math, what I REALLY want is a goddamn THEATRE CLASS!

ps, portia, I called mrs. stowe, and she says the P stands for Pending, not PWNED, but I was close. ;] congrats, babe.

Comment with your honest opinion of me. No matter what it is. Tell me whatever you want. What you love. What you hate. What you remember. What you wish you could forget. My ups. My downs. Anything.

Just post anonymously.

livejournal is so the last thing on my mind nowadays. ok, instant update formula: no american taproom, they're buttheads. no therapeutic recreation, they're bigger buttheads. maybe reston multiplex. depending on whether or not I can find a way to print out the application. jesus. DON'T MOVE, SABAN! getting a job is giving me a headache. never seemed this hard before, and the summer is rapidly disappearing. what's with that? some of you need to get in contact with me and see me before it houdini's itself out of here, kay? gloves. simply dying to find out what my IB scores are... unforchantely, I lost the sheet and my correspondance with Mrs. Stowe to retrieve said sheet has progressed as such: me: uh, can I have my pin number to access my IB scores? mrs. stowe: who are you? me: sorry, this is Laura Grabenstetter. mrs. stowe: don't be sorry! you are wonderful. me: ... thank you. so... about that pin number? mrs. stowe: .... *cricket* me: !?!pleasers!?!? cooper, you were totally right. facebook is totally addictive. Join it, laura. JOIN IT! the devil wants you to, bitch. I ran into Bemish the other day too. crazy. it went much like this: me: bemish!! hey man! bemish: oh... hi. *hug* me: happy birthday! bemish: oh god, please don't start singing. me: oh, ok, heh, I wasn't-- bemish: I've got to go. *run-walk* hrm... I've facebooked him however, and look forward to harrassing him muchly in that realm. ok, out. omg I got a new bathingsuit it is purple and oh so hot. YES!

Whew, I have to say, it is so much easer to reach me/for me to talk to people on email now, partially because of my nomadic lifestyle and partially because you can be so one-on-one with emails. I've really taken to it, guys, and I think I like it better, communication-wise, than ye olde eljay. so... although I do not mean to totally give up eljay any time soon, if you REALLY want to contact me and want me to hear it and respond to it, grabenstetle@vcu.edu People who need to drop me a line: Spud Por-tea-a Der-Rock (yes, the skirt. bwha.) Micheal the True Nomad EMHEN! uuhh more whose names I can't think of right now but FOR GOD'S SAKE PEOPLE DO IT! kthx. XD off to interview-y thing at American Tap Room I'm nervous wish me luck!

I used to live alone before I knew you I've seen your flag on the marble arch, love is not a victory march, it's a cold and its a broken Hallelujah Du hast keine kleidung, Ich habe keine kleidung, Wir haben keine kleidungen. He'd thought about the possibility. In passing. *happy squealing* chesterforever. quite an idea. god. I really kind of want it. Not that I don't already see him everyday already. But. *grin* Yes. I totally would. He protected me against zombies last night, and we made a symphony of the noises in dentists' offices. XD we already get called anoldmarriedcouple all the time. mrah! I want a job at Barnes and Nobles. OOOH Books...

This song is so beautiful... I can't stop listening to it and misting up, whew, I really should be sleeping or getting ready for graduation. Nothing in my house tastes good besides tea. Thank god for Chester or I'd never get around to eating. EPONINE Don't you fret, M'sieur Marius I don't feel any pain A little fall of rain Can hardly hurt me now You're here, that's all I need to know And you will keep me safe And you will keep me close And rain will make the flowers grow. MARIUS You would live a hundred years If I could show you how I won't desert you now... EPONINE The rain can't hurt me now This rain will wash away what's past And you will keep me safe And you will keep me close I'll sleep in your embrace at last. Or as I like to call them, Peppy and Marty. Graduation will be just fine, and I'll go out to dinner afterwards with Chester and Andrewm and maybe Lindsay and Tina and it will be lovely. And they'll cheer me up, and take care of me in a familiar type of way, and I'll feel good again. I am fine, just a little sad.

Graduation Rehearsal today. People are so stupid. Talked for like the first time ever to Jeremy, you know, in German class, who turns out to be very nice and rather shy. He and I are next to each other, as is Dana, which I think kinda speaks about how small our class is. Gilmore Grabenstetter Green that's a lot of gaps. We don't even fill up the seats in the center, and we're having it in our gym. Whoopee. I'm really not overconcerned about graduation, to tell the truth. It'll be tiny and I think I'll probably cry, already every time I look at Andreas and Leatherwood I start getting misty, because people like Laura and Jen I know I'll keep in contact with, stay friends with, but I don't know what's going to happen with Leatherwood and Andreas, becasue I love them a lot, but we really don't talk outside of classes and seeing each other, which wouldn't happen in college and never really happens during the summer. *deep breath* It's making me cry. EEeeesh. Spent all the rest of the day with ChesChes. *smile* we're just so... augh, we're so close. We joke a lot, but we can also talk about serious things and he's really sexy when he's not trying to be. When he's trying (which is never) he is indeed laughable. =P but I love him. Saw pictures of him as a little kid today, along with pictures of his dad. He really does look like him. I feel bad that I never got to meet him. *sigh* I love how Chester takes care of me, especially if he thinks I'm upset. College is going to be honest-to-goodness hard, I miss him when I haven't seen him for a day. Ridiculous. Oh I forgot the part where I nearly didn't graduate. WHEE! Mr. Matey charged me for 2 math books and wouldn't back down, although WHY he'd assign me 2 of the exact same book I don't know and he didn't and it was awful and I cried at him and merideth lent me the $45, which means I now owe her $70, because she covered for me for Cappies Gala which my mom said she'd pay for and didn't and now claims she never promised to pay for. UGH. I feel bad for borrowing so much from Merideth, she's not made of money and why on earth they'd do this I don't know. In any case, it sucked royal ass. And I got yelled at for it at home, because I really don't want them at my graduation anyway and am going out to dinner afterwards with Chester and possibly Jen, but I don't know because she's got a graduation and whatever. I feel like writing poetry, but have nothing in me. Maybe I'll type up an archive of all the poetry Leatherwood and I have written in classes, one line at a time. Some of it is really good. When the word "nostril" comes up, you know the poem's over though. I'll type up something Ben and I wrote, and kudos to whomever guesses who wrote even and who wrote odd... strawberry is never heartfelt. dark juice to make the hardest tart melt stifling in bubbling concentraction--hot and tasteless a sweet blot blood clot bought then wasted seeded into the pink corners of greedy tongues and tonsils burst into a deep green root tangle This isn't going anywhere, but I like the beginning metaphor so much: His coming out was analogous to the death of a fat man. Shooting pains, followed by seizing, clawing girth and the suffocation insulated in his own crippling revulsion. Offensive and lethargic, the initial momentum from chair to knee to sprawled on the panting floor instilled with a halting ignominy. But the eventual stillness was worse, so much worse than the grunting exertion that had preceded it, his weighty problem revealed and stark and no movement left. He told Carlos first, chest expanding in anticipation. Both hands hovered uncomfortably-- four and a half inches from his midsection. Carlos did not stop chain smoking. Under his murky eyes, the realization crystallizing in him throughout his adulthood was blown casually awry with his cheap cigarette smoke.

my last IB today, German, EVERYONE finished after the first 30 minutes of each test (even though it was 2 tests of 1:30 and we weren't allowed to leave until the first hour was up) and on the first test we had a prompt that was an interveiw with Clausi, der Weinachstmann. (Santa Claus, the Christmasman. o.O) Then we had about 40 minutes between the end of that and the beginning of the next test... so Zora, Dray and I jetted to Wendys (mmm chicken!) and got back 5 minutes late for the test, and one of the prompts was like "you hear a noise in the kitchen while babysitting, write a story." So I was babysitting little Adolph and Benito, and we were playing monopoly. Benito wanted everyone to have the same amount of money, and I tried to explain that that wasn't the way the game worked, but he threw a fit and had his way. Adolph was being difficult too, and only wanted to play Risk. So I went to find Risk, and when I came back with it the boys were gone. I heard a strange screaming in the kitchen, and rushed to find out what it was. When I entered I threw my hands in the air and screamed too. Adolph was standing there with a large knife, covered in blood! And said "Froehige Halloween!" Then I hung out and played tekken/crosswords with Andreas and Andrewm, which was bitchin. We went to see Unleashed, which was Jet Li... acting? it was... interesting. I liked it, but I'm not sure if the genre hybrid worked that well, kinda ended up being simplistic on all levels, although a little wrenching. Eh. Morgan Freeman is beast. I'm excited. So excited. I'm going to go through all my clothes, pack properly, leave a note to take me off their taxes as a dependent and leave my parents house. I'm going to stay with Andreas till graduation and possibly till I turn 18 and can change my name. For the first time, on the fence about whether or not I should change my first name. =/ I'll decide later. I have at least that much time. I'll file for no longer being dependent on my parents. I'm so glad. So, just, relieved, and to leave my parents house as well? It's truly a blessing. I'm really thankful to Andrew, and he was so willing with his house. I mean, my mom will still know where I am, she's in contact with his mom, and she'll probably even see me, and try to talk me out of it, and spin it however she wishes. But I'll be free. Especially later when I move to Jen's house, and she and my dad won't be welcome there. We only had to drop 2 people from our one-act, so Dannea and I decided that we'd just fill the roles. It's kinda cool, I get to be the uber bitchy gang leader. Total stretch, considering I run my one-act like a nazi anyway. ;] But it'll be fun.
